text.section:
For the purpose of liquidating an insurer domiciled in a reciprocal state, the domiciliary receiver:
is vested by operation of law with title to all of the property, contracts, and rights of action, and all of the books and records of the insurer located in this State;
immediately may recover balances due from local insurance producers and obtain possession of any books and records of the insurer found in this State;
subject to subsection (c)(1) of this section, may recover other assets of the insurer located in this State; and
may sue in this State to recover any assets of the insurer to which the domiciliary receiver is entitled under the law of this State.
